Description: LCD display controller for Thermalright AIO/cooler screens
 Displays CPU/GPU temperature, usage, frequency and power on the small
 digital LCD screen built into supported Thermalright coolers (e.g. the
 Assassin X 120R Digital), talking to the device over USB HID.
 .
 Includes a systemd user service for the controller daemon, a settings
 GUI for configuring the layout/colours/display mode, and a system tray
 icon showing the live CPU temperature.
 .
 GPU temperature/usage on AMD GPUs requires the optional pyamdgpuinfo
 Python package (not packaged for Debian/Ubuntu); install it with
 "pip install --user pyamdgpuinfo" if needed. NVIDIA GPUs are supported
 out of the box via python3-pynvml.
